The paper deals with the problem of recovering structured solutions to systems of bilinear equations, which is a problem that arises in various areas of computer science and engineering. The paper uses tools from information theory, signal processing, and machine learning to analyze the problem and develop a solution. Therefore, the most likely sub-categories are cs.IT (Information Theory), cs.SP (Signal Processing), and cs.LG (Machine Learning). Additionally, the paper involves numerical optimization and analysis of algorithms, which suggests the sub-categories cs.NA (Numerical Analysis) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks).
